// The Technology Roadmap
//
// Project Thunderkite: STORM's R&D evolution targets, approved by
// the Supreme Leader at the Q2 offsite (volcano-side breakout room B).
//
// Each evolve line is a strategic decision.  Kite Prototype outsources
// at scale because STORM can't manufacture fast enough.  Control Software
// buys an AI Autopilot from a disreputable vendor because building
// in-house would take three more years.
//
// A technology roadmap without evolution targets is just a shopping
// list.  Each arrow must answer: who will supply this at the next
// stage, and what capability does STORM lose or gain?

title Project Thunderkite Roadmap

anchor Supreme Leader [0.97, 0.50]

component Kite Prototype [0.80, 0.20] (build)
component Control Software [0.65, 0.18] (build)
component Carbon Fibre Spars [0.55, 0.45]
component Launch Platform [0.72, 0.35]
component Satellite Uplink [0.45, 0.50]
component String [0.35, 0.70]

// STORM can't scale kite fabrication in-house forever.  Once the
// industrial dirigible market exists, outsource to capture volume.
//
// Any Genesis component built because no supplier existed.  When
// the market catches up, stop building and start buying.
evolve Kite Prototype->Mega Kite Array 0.65 (outsource) label [16, -15]
evolve Control Software->AI Autopilot 0.58 (buy) label [-20, 10]

// Compound decorators: Carbon Fibre evolves toward a market where
// STORM can buy rather than fabricate.  Cloud Uplink replaces the
// bespoke satellite link with a commodity service.
evolve Carbon Fibre Spars 0.78 (market, buy)
evolve Satellite Uplink->Cloud Uplink 0.80 (market, outsource) label [5, -20]

// Decorator on a component shows current sourcing posture
component Hydrogen Envelope [0.80, 0.22] (build)

// Evolve with renaming and decorator â€” the sourcing strategy changes
evolve Hydrogen Envelope->Composite Envelope 0.55 (buy)

Supreme Leader->Kite Prototype
Supreme Leader->Launch Platform
Kite Prototype->Control Software
Kite Prototype->Carbon Fibre Spars
Launch Platform->Satellite Uplink
Control Software->Satellite Uplink
Carbon Fibre Spars->String; surprisingly important
Supreme Leader->Hydrogen Envelope
